Careers — Metrodigi












































































Careers








We believe that great products begin with a great team. Our goal is to be the de facto authoring tool for the creation of digital content that educates, informs, advances, and inspires minds everywhere. We’re always looking for talented and curious people to join us in doing so.  Why Join Metrodigi?The BasicsWe offer competitive salaries, full benefits, 401k program, life insurance, stock options, shiny new mac (whatever else you need to get the job done) The ChallengeContribute to products changing the digital publishing landscape. Work with an intelligent, growing team with a great sense of humor and inspiring leadership with extensive experience in their respective fields. The Perks All work and no play makes us… go a little crazy. Enjoy company outings, happy hours, holiday parties, book clubs, snacks, and all the coffee you can drink (seriously, bring it on).  The OfficeWe have an awesome office overlooking the bay with stunning views of Mt. Tamalpais. It’s easily accessible from most locations in the Bay Area and just a five minute walk from the Larkspur Ferry Terminal. Commuter benefits available.  Open PositionsSenior JavaScript DeveloperMetrodigi, Inc. is currently seeking a qualified JavaScript Developer to work on our eBook team. This position requires the individual to work on-site in our offices in beautiful Marin, but occasional telecommuting is possible after a period of time.  Required Experience and Skills:Demonstrable experience building best of breed, consumer web application interfacesExpert JavaScript/HTML/CSS/AJAX coding skillsFamiliarity with current frontend frameworksExperience programming in one of the following: Python, Perl, or PHPCommand of web standards, CSS based design, cross-browser compatibilityExpertise in one of the following a plus: social media, streaming video, online subscription products, large scale web applicationsIntelligence and a sense of humor to mix in well with a diverse group of bright people

Apply Now
Senior User Experience DesignerMetrodigi is looking for a highly experienced Senior UX Designer for a SaaS cloud-based software solution. This is a full time position primarily focused on developing and improving the visual and user experience of our software. You must be a proactive self-starter with strong interpersonal skills. This is a hands-on visual design role and you must be capable of defining experience models, developing product features, refining the visuals and choreography, and getting into the details all the way from concept to delivery.Responsibilities:Analyze user interface problems and help create solutions that meet measurable business goals and requirementsWork with our team to develop use cases and high-level requirementsAttention to every detail of the user experience (Ensure consistency, simplicity and beauty are at the core of every solution)Develop and maintain detailed user interface specificationsDesign the UI architecture, interface, and interaction flows for the software application for a variety of screen sizes and interaction modelsCreate user-centered designs by considering market analysis, customer feedback, technical constraints/opportunities and usability findingsConduct rapid rounds of usability testing, formulate analyses and action plans for implementationPlan information architecture in conjunction with interactive design, visual design, and navigation developmentPresent design work to senior management and product team for review and feedbackCreate interaction/visual specifications, process flows, wireframes, and visual design mockups as needed to effectively conceptualize and communicate detailed interaction behaviorsNegotiate and articulate the "why" of design decisionsCreate user experience goals, priorities, and deliverables that align with product milestonesSupport development teams throughout the implementation cycleFlexibility is key: design something ridiculously blue sky or something immediately implementableCreate new experience frameworks instead of solely relying on existing paradigmsQualifications:5+ years of experience in UX, interaction design, information architectureStrong portfolio of visualized concepts demonstrating solid processBachelor's Degree or equivalent, preferably in Visual Design or HCIBe a conceptual and detailed thinker, highly detailed in observationDetailed knowledge of user-centric approach to designExpertise in Photoshop, Illustrator, OmniGraffle or other UX/prototyping toolStrong interpersonal, written and oral communication skillsPassion for taking research findings and translate them into tangible designsFamiliarity with technical considerations when designing a cloud-based solution

Apply Now
Senior Product ManagerMetrodigi is looking for a highly experienced Product Manager for our SaaS cloud-based software solution for creating eBooks. This is a full time position primarily focused on managing existing products and services as well as creating and integrating new products and product changes. You will lead regularly scheduled meetings centered on system and operational requirements for product changes and new product development. You will conducts margin analysis, industry/market research, and in-life performance measurement to determine product demand, positioning, viability, and profitability. You will also create formal business cases and product descriptions and work as a facilitator between the various internal organizations to ensure product policy and processes are negotiated, documented, and accurately executed. You will work with an engineering counterpart to define product release requirements.Responsibilities:Work with our team to develop use cases and requirements documentation for current and future features/productsAnalyze problems and help create solutions that meet measurable business goals and requirementsShepherd the product and support development teams throughout the implementation cycleIdentify and present innovative and creative product solutionsChallenge assumptions, collect usage data, and recommend strategies Clarify, document and shepherd business requirements to implementationConduct research and gather requirements from clients, users, and internal stakeholdersWork with Product Owner to develop a product plan, roadmap and strategyParticipate in and coordinate with marketing effortsAnalyzing potential partner relationships for the productProject management of all product integration/launches/changes throughout implementationAssist in the development of marketing plans and effortsAssist in the creation of user documentation and liaise with the support teamMay require some travelQualifications:5+ years of experience in Saas product management, product development, strategic planning and implementationBachelor's Degree or equivalent (preferably in CS or engineering)2+ years of spreadsheet-based numerical analysis, business casesStrong technical acumen in web-based programming languagesFamiliarity with technical considerations when designing a cloud-based solutionStrong portfolio of successful productsA conceptual and detailed thinker, highly detailed in observationStrong interpersonal, written and oral communication skillsBe pro-active and a motivated self-starter in a fast-paced environment

Apply Now
















